                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18410405-1224-offence-1 t18410405-name-1258"></join>Robert Watt</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-1259" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1259" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1259" type="surname" value="HARMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1259" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES HARMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Robert Watt. On Monday, the 5th of April, about five o'clock in the afternoon, the prisoner came with Melon, and offered some irons in pledge—I noticed one of them snatch down a petticoat, but they stood so close together, I could not say which it was—I saw Read with the lower part of her person, raise the petticoat, and put it under her arm—I sent a lad for a policeman, who came, and I then said to the prisoner, "Give up that petticoat"—they both cried out, "What do you mean? what petticoat?"—I said, "The petticoat under your arm"—she immediately dropped it from under her arm, and was taken into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I never saw the petticoat—it was never in my possession—there were other persons in the shop. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> There was one other per<lb></lb>son at the other end of the shop—I saw it drop from her person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410405-name-1260" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1260" type="surname" value="HOLLAND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410405-name-1260" type="given" value="GEORGE WATERLOO"></interp>GEORGE WATERLOO HOLLAND</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I was fetched, and saw the prisoner drop the petticoat from under her left arm, under her shawl—I saw it distinctly fall from her—I picked it up, and took her into custody.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
